  "description": {
    "en": "**Classic Sidecar Variation**\n\nA sophisticated and potent cocktail featuring:\n*   Equal parts spirits and citrus\n*   Slightly sweeter than a Sidecar due to the rum\n*   A complex blend of flavors that are both refreshing and boozy.",
    "zh": "**\u7d93\u5178\u5074\u8eca\u8b8a\u594f**\n\n\u4e00\u6b3e\u7cbe\u7dfb\u800c\u5f37\u52c1\u7684\u96de\u5c3e\u9152\uff0c\u7279\u8272\uff1a\n*   \u7b49\u6bd4\u4f8b\u7684\u70c8\u9152\u548c\u67d1\u6a58\n*   \u7531\u65bc\u862d\u59c6\u9152\u7684\u7de3\u6545\uff0c\u6bd4\u5074\u8eca\u7565\u751c\n*   \u6e05\u65b0\u4e14\u6fc3\u70c8\u7684\u8907\u96dc\u98a8\u5473\u878d\u5408\u3002"
  },
  "historical_reference": {
    "en": "**Origin**: First appeared in the 1930s.\n\n*   Often attributed to Harry MacElhone of Harry's New York Bar in Paris.\n*   A variation of the Sidecar cocktail.\n*   Name suggests a risque connotation.",
